We recommend that management implement minimum standard requirements for segregation and storage of solid waste pending collection and their final disposal to the dumpsite, as follows:

Separate containers/receptacles for all types of wastes shall be maintained from all sources;

These containers must be properly marked/identified for on-site collections such as compostable, non-recyclable, special waste and/or any other classification as may be determined by the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board;

Maintain receptacles and Material   Recovery Facility for temporary placement of solid wastes; and

Convert the open dump to a controlled dump site

