We recommend management:
To direct the concerned officials and employees to liquidate immediately their cash advances in compliance with Section 89 of PD 1445;
Send demand letters to concerned officials and employees to enforce immediate settlement of the outstanding cash advances;
In the event that the officials and employees concerned failed to settle/liquidate their cash advances after written demand, we strongly recommend towithhold their salaries and/or other benefits due to them notwithstanding the imposition of other sanctions provided for under COA Circular No.2012-004 dated November 28, 2012.

We recommend that Management:
a. Reactivate or create a new Inventory Committee composed of a representative each from the Mayor’s Office, from the Municipal Treasurer’s Office and a representative from each department to prepare the necessary procedures in the proper and orderly conduct of the physical count of the all the property, plant and equipment and inventories owned by the Municipality;
b. Require the Inventory Committee to conduct the physical count of all the properties recorded in the books and those not yet recorded but actually found in the LGU offices/premises and to prepare the corresponding inventory reports thereof in accordance with the prescribed format (See Annex 49 - Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment) of the NGAS Manual;
c. Prepare and submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) and the Report of the Physical Count of Inventories (RCPI) to the Auditor, at least annually, after reconciliation with accounting records as provided by law and regulations.

We recommend that management comply the following:

Require the accountable officers immediate liquidation of long outstanding cash advances in compliance with COA Circular 97-002, otherwise withhold the salaries of the concerned officials and employees notwithstanding the imposition of other sanctions provided for under Section Nos. 9.2 and 9.3 of the same Circular;

Send follow-up and demand letters requiring the personnel concerned to liquidate. For those no longer connected with the Municipality, the demand letters should be sent to their present address or stations;

No additional cash advance to personnel unless their previous cash advance are first liquidated and/or settled;

Adherence to the provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 in the grant, use and liquidation of cash advance.

